      },
      "date": "2012-06-26 14:38:46.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nOne note about a patch like this - it is much more valuable to make a simple commit at the end of your current patch series instead of a large patch that duplicates the existing patches. That ensures the code being tested matches the code that was submitted.\n\nIf it is combining multiple branches, then it could be a merge or two that combines the branches. Any earlier merge patches in such a series can be marked in the commit message to exclude testing:\n\n Test-Parameters: fortestonly testlist=\"\"\n\n(please see Test-Parameters wiki to confirm syntax).",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
